><figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/987835d/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/320x213!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4dfe9e0/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/568x379!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/dd7d713/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/768x512!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/d2be307/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/1080x720!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 1080w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/22f6b2e/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/1240x826!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 1240w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/bdd93c7/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/1440x960!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 1440w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/de1fccc/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/2160x1440!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 2160w"  sizes="100vw"  >     <img class="image" alt="Retired fighter Hector Lizarraga leans against the ropes of a boxing ring dressed in a red shirt. "  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/7089c36/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/320x213!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/cb2aa16/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/568x379!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/f77e4e1/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/768x512!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/a99fff4/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/1080x720!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 1080w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/76b7523/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/1240x826!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 1240w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/281b0a1/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/1440x960!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 1440w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/7c540a5/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/2160x1440!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg 2160w"  sizes="100vw"    width="2000"   height="1333"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/6f1c78e/2147483647/strip/true/crop/5472x3648+0+0/resize/2000x1333!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2Feb%2F5b897fde47f49b77feae76a71b82%2F1263003-me-0408-lizarraga-rcg-1080.jpg" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-caption" >Héctor Lizárraga empezó a boxear de adolescente para defenderse de los que lo molestaban y se enamoró de este deporte. Le deben la pensión de boxeador. </div><div class="figure-credit">(Robert Gauthier / Los Angeles Times)</div> </div>  </figure></div><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Anuncio</div><div id="google-adae19f649-e3b6-4f64-93aa-a0849671fb19" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/espanol/california/storylongform_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;5&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p>Fueron las burlas de otros adolescentes las que llevaron a Héctor Lizárraga al boxeo. A los 16 años, no estaba seguro de dónde podría aprender a pelear, pero estaba seguro de que necesitaba aprender muy bien.</p><p>Su padre hacía tiempo que se había marchado y la muerte de su madre en Mexicali le llevó a cruzar la frontera entre México y California con su hermana mayor. No fue una vida fácil en Estados Unidos. No hablaba inglés y se estaba adaptando a una nueva escuela en Fresno. Al mismo tiempo, trabajaba como jornalero recogiendo fresas y uvas en el Valle Central.</p><p>Y entonces llegaron los acosadores.</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-right
    
>   <div class="column-container one-column-container" data-click="1col" >  <div class="column-container-row one-column-container-row">  <div class="column-container-column one-column-container-column"> <div data-element="rich-text-module" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"  data-module-id="00000188-0377-df35-a588-43776f5c0000" >  <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/10e7413/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/320x480!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/583bff4/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/568x852!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/b59e362/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/768x1152!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/5d29a8a/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1080x1620!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 1080w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/8df6835/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1240x1860!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 1240w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/987df9a/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1440x2160!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 1440w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/2c4bdf6/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/2160x3240!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 2160w"  sizes="100vw"  >     <img class="image" alt="Fight poster: HECTOR LIZARRAGA, FEATHERWEIGHT, 1985-2003, 38-12-5 (21 KOs). PENSION OWED: $39,000"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/02678ba/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/320x480!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/95d9f5d/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/568x852!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/868627f/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/768x1152!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/f809112/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1080x1620!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 1080w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/a3827f8/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1240x1860!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 1240w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/fc4044c/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1440x2160!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 1440w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/c6b9e00/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/2160x3240!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg 2160w"  sizes="100vw"    width="2000"   height="3000"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4d8bab0/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/2000x3000!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F67%2Fa6%2Fcfbcc3084397bf0516ce3f3fc38d%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-hectorlizarraga.jpg" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   </figure></div><p></p>  </div><aside class="answerbox-module" data-click="answerBox"  data-module-id="00000188-0380-d291-af9b-8bef27c00000"><header class="answerbox-header">  <div class="answerbox-group">    </div></header><div class="answerbox-body">  <ps-toggler class="toggle-text" data-toggle="bodyText" data-toggle-enabled ><div class="toggle-text-content ct-rich-text-children body-1" data-toggle-content> <div class="answerbox-row answerbox-1-column"><div class="answerbox-column"> <div data-element="rich-text-module" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"  data-module-id="00000188-0380-d246-afaf-7b9960ca0000" >  <p>Lizarraga was a champion featherweight nicknamed “Papi,” known for his toughness in the ring and a deadly body shot. His professional career, however, didn’t start off well, posting a 5-7-3 losing record before changing managers twice and going on a streak of 31-1-2.</p><p>That win streak included Lizarraga defeating favored fighter Welcome Ncita of South Africa in 1997 to win the International Boxing Federation’s World Championship in the featherweight division.</p><p></p><p>“People have the wrong idea about boxing,” Lizarraga said. “They think that boxing is dangerous, and people do get hurt, but boxing is more than that. There is discipline and hard work. I was able to follow instructions in the ring and that’s what made me successful.”</p>  </div> </div></div> </div><div class="toggle-text-text-block" data-toggle-button-container><a href="#" class="toggle-text-more text-preview" data-toggle-trigger="bodyText"><svg class="icon chevron-icon"><use xlink:href="#chevron"></use></svg><span class="more-text">MOSTRAR MÁS</span><span class="less-text">MOSTRAR MENOS</span><svg class="icon chevron-icon"><use xlink:href="#chevron"></use></svg></a></div></ps-toggler>  </div><footer class="answerbox-footer"></footer></aside> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p>“Pensé que necesitaba aprender a pelear”, dijo. “Pensé en la lucha libre, pero me parecía falsa, y el karate era caro”.</p><p>Encontró un entrenador de boxeo que trabajaba en los mismos campos.</p><p>“Simplemente me enamoré del boxeo”, dice Lizárraga, que acabó abandonando la escuela para ganar más dinero trabajando en el campo. Pero no abandonó el boxeo. Era metódico con su entrenamiento, estudioso en el ring. Para Lizárraga, el boxeo era algo más que un torbellino de golpes.</p><p>“Es como jugar al ajedrez”, dijo Lizárraga, cuyo apodo en el ring era “Papi”.</p><p>Dejó los campos para pelear por todo el país, y ganó el título mundial del peso pluma de la IBF durante una larga carrera profesional de 18 años que terminó en 2003. Pero cuatro meses después de su último combate, sus ganancias del boxeo se agotaban peligrosamente. Y se dio cuenta de que su futuro, sin estudios ni experiencia laboral, era sombrío.</p><p>Había vuelto a Fresno, donde mucha gente le conocía. Le llamaban campeón.</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Anuncio</div><div id="google-adae8a0efe-43bc-4e36-804f-71619c1ade78" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/espanol/california/storylongform_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;6&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p>“Llamé a un conocido y le dije que buscaba trabajo”, cuenta Lizárraga. “Pensó que estaba bromeando”.</p><p>Al día siguiente, el campeón estaba repartiendo tortillas.</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
