x3240!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg 2160w"  sizes="100vw"  >     <img class="image" alt="Fight poster for JENIFER ALCORN. LIGHTWEIGHT, 1999-2003, 18-0 (11 KOs), PENSION OWED: $6,300"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4713ab1/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/320x480!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/2a96be9/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/568x852!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/d31373b/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/768x1152!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/b5645bc/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1080x1620!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg 1080w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/764ab39/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1240x1860!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg 1240w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/ec1d99d/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/1440x2160!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg 1440w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/dff58cf/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/2160x3240!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg 2160w"  sizes="100vw"    width="2000"   height="3000"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/febe693/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1440x2160+0+0/resize/2000x3000!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9c%2F02%2F97477ca8405e9932b5946d61f6d3%2Fme-boxers-pensions-fight-card-jeniferalcorn-new.jpg" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   </figure></div><p></p>  </div><aside class="answerbox-module" data-click="answerBox"  data-module-id="00000188-0392-df35-a588-43f655200000"><header class="answerbox-header">  <div class="answerbox-group">    </div></header><div class="answerbox-body">  <ps-toggler class="toggle-text" data-toggle="bodyText" data-toggle-enabled ><div class="toggle-text-content ct-rich-text-children body-1" data-toggle-content> <div class="answerbox-row answerbox-1-column"><div class="answerbox-column"> <div data-element="rich-text-module" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"  data-module-id="00000188-0392-d246-afaf-7b9b7b6d0000" >  <p>Alcorn’s nickname was “All American” when she swept into boxing at 27. The champion featherweight won all 18 of her professional bouts — 11 by knockout. In 2003, she famously beat Mia St. John, who was the face of women’s boxing at the time.</p><p>“I was a wife and a mother prior to being a boxer and so it wasn’t something that I was doing knowing that it was going to be my life,” Alcorn said. “It opened up doors in my community to allow me to have a fitness business afterward.”</p><p>Alcorn said she enjoyed training and competing, but also saw boxing as a way to show others that hard work paves the way for success.</p><p>“A lot of people get into fighting because they’re paying the bills and they’re hoping to be that next big person,” Alcorn said. “I did it because I’ve always been an athlete. I didn’t do it for the money.”</p>  </div> </div></div> </div><div class="toggle-text-text-block" data-toggle-button-container><a href="#" class="toggle-text-more text-preview" data-toggle-trigger="bodyText"><svg class="icon chevron-icon"><use xlink:href="#chevron"></use></svg><span class="more-text">MOSTRAR MÁS</span><span class="less-text">MOSTRAR MENOS</span><svg class="icon chevron-icon"><use xlink:href="#chevron"></use></svg></a></div></ps-toggler>  </div><footer class="answerbox-footer"></footer></aside> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p>Pero la euforia se convirtió rápidamente en enojo. ¿Por qué nadie se lo había dicho? Alcorn sabe que no es difícil encontrarla. No se movió del sitio durante muchos años después de terminar su carrera como boxeadora, creando un exitoso negocio de fitness y enseñando este deporte a los atletas de Fresno State como forma de aumentar la fortaleza mental y la concentración. Alcorn se trasladó a Oregón hace seis años con su marido, sin haber oído hablar nunca de la pensión para boxeadores. Ella es una de las pocas mujeres a las que se les debe la prestación.</p><p>“Sinceramente, hoy en día es muy fácil localizar a la gente”, afirma Alcorn, de 52 años, que trabaja como directora ejecutiva de la South Coast Humane Society de Brookings (Oregón), donde tiene una sólida presencia en las redes sociales.</p><p>Alcorn descubrió tarde el boxeo y se hizo profesional a los 27 años. Su marido, que trabajaba en las fuerzas del orden, hizo las veces de entrenador y, mientras criaban a su familia, trabajaban en el ring. Alcorn fue tres veces campeona mundial de peso ligero, invicta en sus 18 combates.</p><p>“Cuando mis hijos empezaron a practicar atletismo, supe que había llegado el momento de retirarme”, afirma.</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
